shePhysical.name: shePhysical

revisions.description: Change PIU-Types for Modules
New notifications for shePhysCardPlugged and sheEntPhysCardUnplugged. Add shePhysPortUserLabel to portTable and corresponding control-group.
Change PIU-Types for acceptable cards again (without M:). Change syntax for UserLabel in shePhysPortTable to OctetString (0..40).
Correct typo for shePhysContainerAccCardTypes.
Add PIU-Types for infineon based IUADSL:72 and CXU_C to shePhysContainerAccCardTypes. Change syntax for all ControlTimeStamp to U32 and unit sec.
Change description for shePhysCardProtDynamicRole.

Add external alarms to shePhysShelfAlarm-notificationgroup. Add configuration and status entrys for external alarm inputs and outputs to shePhysShelfTable and shePhysShelfControl-group. Add new configuration request and result event for this external alarm configuration's.
Add new attribute to configure special redundancy features for CXU.
Add new trap shePhysRedundancyFeatureModified. Change syntax for shePhysCardTemperatureCurrent to integer. Add enum value for default shePhysCardUpgradeState.
Increase length of OctedString for PortUserLabel to 100.
Take over by Gerd Barchmann for R2.5. Base was she MIB release 151.
Correct info about usable Shelftype's. Add new CardTypes to shePhysContainerAccCardType. Use TemperatureWarning-Alarm from VSHE only.

Add some removed elements for backward compatibility of the managment system. The NE release up R2.5 will still NOT support this elements, but some used OID has been moved! Add card types of power modules for shelf M1100:E and G1100:E.
Correct possible shelftype list.
Add IU:ADSL:48 for backward copatibility reason's.
New IU board IU_VDSL24P supported.
Add new shelftype G400:E.
New IU boards IU_VDSL48P, IU_VDSL48I and IU_10x1G supported. New CXU boards CXU_C2 and CXU_B2 supported.
Add shePhysPortNeInfo to support ACI licensing feature.
Support of shelf G400:R:A and additional power modules.
Expand shePhysPortUserLabel to 200 byte.
Expand range for shePhysContainerAccCardTypes.
New powermodul PM:R:A supported.

Add support for new ISDN service boards. Add parameter for relative humidity status and alarm threshold configuration to shePhysShelfTable and corresponding threshold alarm to shePhysShelfAlarms group. Modify description for shePhysShelfMupState1 / 2 alarms. Add new shePhysShelfHeatExchangerIn / Out alarms.
Add support for new ADSL2+ and SHDSL service boards (only first integration). Add support for new 72-Port VoIP over POTS Service Module.
Add new central board CXU_B22 and CXU_B3 support.
Add support for Shelf-types G600 and MDUS. Add support for Card-types CXU_M and SB_XDSL (hiX5622). Correct description of fanAlarms (depends on used shelftype).

Add shePhysPortNEInfo for ISDNPorts. Add parameter for BatteryBackup configuration in hix5622 system. Modify comments for usage of external alarms in hix5622. Add new alarm shePhysCardSWVersionProblem. Correct Mnemocode for CXU_M (hix5622).
Correct description for fan-alarms to support hix5622.
Add support for Card-type IU1GE:10O:SYN:E.
Add new shelftype G600:R:E.
Remove not supported 1GE board. Add new ADSL72 CGH board for Annex J support only.
Add new card types for CXU and IU's. Not all of them are supported by all releases! Add new Subtypes for Shelf G1100 and M1100 with first support in R2.8.
Add module for hiX5608. New RejResult value for port control.

Remove not longer supported board CXU_B22. New shelftypes G100 and G200 supported. Add new parameter to shelfTable for alarmoutput switching. Add new parameter to portTable for timestamp info of last state changes. Define default usage of ExternalAlarm01 for hiX5608.
New card and powermodules supported by R3.7M.

Add missing shelf type definitions for G1100:A and M600:DF:E. Add new IU types for support in R3.7M version. Add new 2G shelftypes also for support in R2.8 maintenance. Add new 2G powermodules used with 2G shelftypes.
Update list of supported cards for R3.7M.
Correct mnemocode for new 2G powermodule. Correct mnemocode for new 2G shelftype. Add G200S 2G shelftype. Add new IUSHDSL:48E:8Q:E board.
Correct mnemocode list for IU's supported with R3.7M.
Set parameter shePhysCardUpgradeState to obsolete state.
Add new Shelf-Alarm shePhysShelfExtAlarmCollectorNotConnected.

shePhysCardTable.name: shePhysCardTable
shePhysCardTable.description: Table containing the plug-in unit entries.

shePhysCardEntry.name: shePhysCardEntry
shePhysCardEntry.description: Entry of shePhysCardTable. Each entry is used to represent a card independently whether it is present or not (feature offline configuration). Cards can be created either by auto-configuration (plug-in) or by user command. Notifications : shePhysStateChangeOper. shePhysStateChangeAdmin. shePhysCardCreated. shePhysCardDeleted. Alarm traps when a fault has been detected or cleared.

shePhysCardAdminState.name: shePhysCardAdminState
shePhysCardAdminState.description: This attribute shows the administrative state of the plugin unit. In the transition from lock to unlock the plug-in unit is diagnosed. Default is notEquipped except for controller cards. The AdminState of controller cards is always unlocked. Planned is very similar to the locked state. Planned is used for configuration of cards without having a card equipped. A correct card being plugged leads to an auto-configuration of the card: the AdminState changes automatically from planned to unlocked.

shePhysCardAvailState.name: shePhysCardAvailState
shePhysCardAvailState.description: The availability state of a card.

shePhysCardOperState.name: shePhysCardOperState
shePhysCardOperState.description: The operational state of a card.

shePhysCardProtCapability.name: shePhysCardProtCapability
shePhysCardProtCapability.description: The protection modes the card can work: -bit0=1: Card can work as standalone card. -bit1=1: Card can work as standby card.

shePhysCardProtMode.name: shePhysCardProtMode
shePhysCardProtMode.description: The redundancy mode the card is running. -standaloneCard: The card works as standalone board. No redundancy is supported. -protectionCard: The card works in redundancy mode.

shePhysCardProtDefaultRole.name: shePhysCardProtDefaultRole
shePhysCardProtDefaultRole.description: Defines the default role of the card (e.g. after power on) if more than one card which belong to the same protection group are become availible at the same time. Note, this attribute is only valid if shePhysCardProtCapability = protectionCard. -working: The card becomes the active card by default. -protecting: The card becomes the standby card by default.

shePhysCardProtDynamicRole.name: shePhysCardProtDynamicRole
shePhysCardProtDynamicRole.description: The dynamic role of card. Note, this attribute is only valid if shePhysCardProtMode = protectionCard. -active: The card is the active card. -standby: The card is the standby card. -notDefined: If there is no card plugged, it is not possible to say which card will become the active or standby card.

shePhysCardProtGroupId.name: shePhysCardProtGroupId
shePhysCardProtGroupId.description: The ID of protection group this card belongs to. Cards with the same Id can protect each other. Note, this attribute is only valid if shePhysCardProtCapability = protectionCard.

shePhysCardProtState.name: shePhysCardProtState
shePhysCardProtState.description: The current state of the protection: -unknown If the dynamic role of the cards which belong to a protection group is not set yet, there is no information about the protection state available. -active_noRedundancy: The card is the active card but is not protected by a standby card. -active_protected: The card is the active card is is protected by a standby card. -active_degraded: The card is the active card but not all functionality is protected by the standby card. -standby_notPresent: The card is the standby card but it is not available. -standby_booting: The card is the standby card but is still booting. -standby_protecting: The card is the standby card and protects the active card. -standby_degraded: The card is the standby card but can not take over all functionality of the current active board. Note, this attribute is only valid if shePhysCardProtCapability = protectionCard.

shePhysCardAlarmSeverityIndex.name: shePhysCardAlarmSeverityIndex

shePhysCardUpgradeState.name: shePhysCardUpgradeState

NOTE: The parameter is set to obsolete state with R3.7M. Also former releases does not report a valid information on this parameter. Valid informations about SW upgrade could only be retrieved via sheSystemSwMaintenanceTaskTable.

shePhysCardTemperatureCurrent.name: shePhysCardTemperatureCurrent

shePhysCardControlRequest.name: shePhysCardControlRequest
shePhysCardControlRequest.description: The card commands : changeAdminState: changes the shePhysCardAdminState of a card. AdminState of controller cards cannot be changed. changeAlarmSeverityProfile: changes the shePhysCardAlarmSeverityIndex of a card. This is the pointer to a alarm severity profile. createCard: creates plugin units. Acceptable in state NotEquipped and when object does not exist. The AdminState after creation, possible values are Planned or Locked, is specified as command parameter. The command is not accepted for CXUs. These HW objects are automatically created. The acceptable CardTypes are specified in the slot attribute shePhysContainerAccCardTypes. The content of this attribute changes after the creation to values allowed for the convert command. deleteCard: deletes a card. Acceptable only in state Planned/Locked. The command is not accepted for CXUs. CXUs are automatically deleted when board redundancy is disabled. The AdminState changes to NotEquipped. convertCard: converts the type of card. Acceptable only within the same card group, e.g. ADSL to ADSL according to content of types listed in shePhysContainerAccCardTypes. convertCard allowed in state Planned/Locked. Notifications: shePhysCardControlResult when a command has finished. reset commands: resetSystem: reset of system (all cards) and activates loads after SW download. The main card will perform a restart. resetSystemWithDefaultConf : restart with default configuration is performed. resetCard: after SW download to activate the new load of a specific card. resetCardAllOfType: after SW download of cards of the same type to activate the new load. Notifications : shePhysCardReset at beginning of reset. shePhysCardResetEnd at end of reset. shePhysCardControlResult for reset of CXU in case of a failure occured after the reset has been accepted. changeAlarmSeverityProfile: the alarm severity profile is changed for a specific card. THIS REQUEST WILL NOT LONGER BE SUPPORTED BY NE R2.5: setTemperatureThreshold: configure the temperature threshold which is used. When temperature reaches the threshold, alarm is turned on.

shePhysFanAlarm5.name: shePhysFanAlarm5

shePhysShelfExternalAlarm01.description: External Alarm 01. Default usage in hix5622 R1.0 system (shelftyp MDUS:E): AC Failure -> Powering Alarm - Loss of external power.

shePhysShelfExternalAlarm03.name: shePhysShelfExternalAlarm03
shePhysShelfExternalAlarm03.description: External Alarm 3. Default usage in hix5622 system R1.0 (shelftyp MDUS:E): Deep battery discharge -> Battery Low - battery is provisioned and present but voltage is too low.

shePhysShelfExternalAlarm04.name: shePhysShelfExternalAlarm04
shePhysShelfExternalAlarm04.description: External Alarm 4. Default usage in hix5622 R1.0 system (shelftyp MDUS:E): Battery missing -> Battery is provisioned but missing.

shePhysShelfExternalAlarm05.name: shePhysShelfExternalAlarm05

shePhysShelfExternalAlarm06.name: shePhysShelfExternalAlarm06

shePhysShelfHeatExchangerIn.description: Break down of 1 or more fan of the heat exchanger inner circle. Note: This alarm could only occur in case of used shelftype G400R/G600:R:E with plugged PM_R module.

shePhysCardDeletionStarted.name: shePhysCardDeletionStarted

shePhysCardConvertionStarted.description: The card convertion procedure in the NE was started.

shePhysCardPlugged.name: shePhysCardPlugged
shePhysCardPlugged.description: A card was plugged. This notification contains a list of two entPhysicalIndices. First is the entPhysicalIndex of the slot, were these module was plugged and the second, the entPhysicalIndex of the card itself.

shePhysCardUnplugged.name: shePhysCardUnplugged
shePhysCardUnplugged.description: A card was unplugged. This notification contains a list of two entPhysicalIndices. First is the entPhysicalIndex of the slot, were these module was plugged before and the second, the entPhysicalIndex of the card itself.

shePhysCardChangedTemperatureThreshold.name: shePhysCardChangedTemperatureThreshold

shePhysCardTemperaturePowerDown.description: Temperature alarm. The IU has detect high temperature and start's first action to reduce power consumption.

shePhysCardOverTemperatureReset.name: shePhysCardOverTemperatureReset
shePhysCardOverTemperatureReset.description: CXU has forced IU-Card to reset because of over temperature.

shePhysCardOverTemperatureThreshold.name: shePhysCardOverTemperatureThreshold
shePhysCardOverTemperatureThreshold.description: Card temperature Threshold alarm. THIS ELEMENT WILL NOT LONGER BE SUPPORTED BY NE up R2.5.

shePhysCardTemperatureWarning.name: shePhysCardTemperatureWarning
shePhysCardTemperatureWarning.description: Temperature warning alarm. The CXU has detected a higher temperature then the configured value.

shePhysCardSWVersionProblem.name: shePhysCardSWVersionProblem
shePhysCardSWVersionProblem.description: Card out of service due to wrong SW version. Please upgrade!

shePhysPortAdminStateChanged.name: shePhysPortAdminStateChanged
shePhysPortAdminStateChanged.description: The ports adminState changed. Could be send as a collection trap. That means, this notification could contain more then one indexed ifAdminState. During system startup normaly a large number of notifications are needed. In such a case, it is possible to send only one notification per card which contain the ifAdminStates of all port's.

shePhysPortOperStateChanged.name: shePhysPortOperStateChanged
shePhysPortOperStateChanged.description: The ports operational state changed. Could be send as a collection trap. That means, this notification could contain more then one indexed ifOperState. During system startup normaly a large number of notifications are needed. In such a case, it is possible to send only one notification per card which contain the ifOperStates of all port's.

shePhysPortControlResult.name: shePhysPortControlResult
shePhysPortControlResult.description: Notification of port command ending and result.

shePhysPortCreated.name: shePhysPortCreated
shePhysPortCreated.description: Notification about port creation. Could be send as a collection trap. That means, this notification could contain more then one ifIndex. In case of a card creation sequence, normaly a large number of PortCreated-notifications are needed. In such a case, it is possible to send only one notification which contain the ifIndeces of all created port's for the entPhysicalIndex of this new card.

shePhysPortDeleted.name: shePhysPortDeleted
shePhysPortDeleted.description: Notification about the succesfull delete of a port. Could be send as a collection trap. That means, this notification could contain more then one ifIndex. In case of a card deletion sequence, normaly a large number of PortDeleted-notifications are needed. In such a case, it is possible to send only one notification which contain the ifIndeces of all deleted port's for the entPhysicalIndex of this card.

shePhysPortOperStateDown.name: shePhysPortOperStateDown
shePhysPortOperStateDown.description: This is a operstate-down alarm trap. This trap could not be send as collection trap (different from OperStateChanged - Event trap)!! This trap could be blocked by setting in alarmseverity-profile.

Systemversion -> Shelftypes SHE hiX5635 -> M1200:E, M1100:E, G1100:E, G1100:A, G1100:B:E SHE hiX5630 -> M600:E, G600:E, G600:R:E, M600:DF:E SHE hiX5625 -> M400:E, G400:E, G400:R:A, SHE hiX5622 R1.0 -> MDUS:E (obsolete because release was canceled) SHE hiX5608 -> 'empty' string because no shelf is used, single box system Shelftype's 2 generation - only new 2G powermodules could be used!
